Class CompetitorPositionOffsetData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.Attachments

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeObject>

    public class CompetitorPositionOffsetData
extends TimeObject
    An instance of this class represents an offset position for a Competitor.

    The static method subscribe(com.tractrac.clientmodule.Race, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.ICallbackData<com.tractrac.clientmodule.RaceCompetitor, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.CompetitorPositionOffsetData>, long, long) can be used to receive positions.

    Custom data may be attached to each position instance.

        public static com.maptrack.client.io.TypeController subscribe(Race race,
                                              ICallbackData<RaceCompetitor,CompetitorPositionOffsetData> callback,
                                              long fromTime,
                                              long toTime)
        Subscribes to snapped competitor positions for a given Race.

        The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to a given callback, as they are received.

        The returned type controller should be added to a DataController.

        Parameters:
        race - the race from which to request the data
        callback - the callback to receive the positions
        fromTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested from this time
        toTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested before this time
        Returns:
        the type controller
